Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.24,0:00:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruhenheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ludwig!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.30,0:02:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you barking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that bike\Nbreakdown again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.61,0:02:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The chain always\Ncomes loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.68,0:02:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected, bulky trash left at\Na trash pick-up isn't any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.89,0:02:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like\Nbulky trash to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.03,0:02:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When I ride it,\Neveryone says,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.99,0:02:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's trash.\NTrash is moving by."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.43,0:02:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"Trash is riding by on trash"'\Nthey say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.63,0:02:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true. It's a wonderful\Nfive-speed super cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.54,0:02:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see it.\NLet's adjust it one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.11,0:02:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. It looks like\Nthere's a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.09,0:02:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He called earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.63,0:02:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... You had a reservation?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.13,0:03:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. My name is Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.30,0:03:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mr. Lunge,\Nthank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.94,0:03:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that a room was open\Non such short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we always\Nhave openings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.84,0:03:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it still the off-season?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like an off-season\Nall year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The only guests staying here\Nright now are that couple over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.72,0:03:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The man's legs are bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.36,0:03:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems like they've had\Na rough time on their trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.93,0:03:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take his bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.33,0:03:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I leave it to you Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's room 302.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.00,0:03:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the view\Nfrom that room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I've given you the room\Nwith the best view.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave your bags here,\Nokay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it looks\Nlike trash, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.39,0:03:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.89,0:04:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a pretty\Nwonderful bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.26,0:04:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge of the BKA?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here at\Nthis rural police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.27,0:04:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was wondering how many more\Nofficers I could gather for backup here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Backup? More officers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, If you asked\Nthe state police,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.48,0:04:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they could supply you with quite\Na few officers in under an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.71,0:04:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that a situation like\Nthat would happen in a rural town like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, you should start checking\Neveryone who comes into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.36,0:04:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Before something\Nterrible happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good ! Just like that!\NIt's running well!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.04,0:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Speeding up!\NChanging gears!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.38,0:04:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, trash?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:04:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the trash still move?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an eyesore!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Trash, trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.53,0:05:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.91,0:05:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you traveling\Nby yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.32,0:05:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this for work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's private.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.49,0:05:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Aren't you lonely\Nby yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.49,0:05:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.76,0:05:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I have family.\NMy daughter had a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You have a grandchild?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.90,0:05:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandchildren are nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Our grandchild always\Nthinks about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I'm writing them\Na postcard now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.61,0:06:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Letters are nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.91,0:06:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can write things that you would\Nnever be able to say in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.89,0:06:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?\NCare to write one, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.46,0:06:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter to my grandson...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.46,0:06:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I write?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.60,0:06:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could only draw...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm, excuse me.\NCan I stay here for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved me.\NI was enjoying a relaxing picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got lost along the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.39,0:06:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I finally reached this town,\Nit was already late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.66,0:06:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a lifesaver.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.24,0:07:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No one got off at\Nthis town, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.21,0:07:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.22,0:07:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't sound like a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.42,0:07:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It definitely sounded\Nlike a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No one in this town has a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.80,0:07:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they did,\Nit's probably that drunk out back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It would make a larger sound\Nif it were out back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.24,0:07:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, that drunk\Nwouldn't hit anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.44,0:07:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't hit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.11,0:07:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.51,0:07:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost again because of\Nyour unlucky talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.02,0:07:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! It's not my fault!\NStop playing the lottery!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludwig...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludwig...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:07:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludwig...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.26,0:08:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My Ludwig isn't anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something that\Nsounded like a gunshot earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.44,0:08:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that\Nmy Ludwig was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My baby was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.31,0:08:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Mrs. Hillman.\NThere was no gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.31,0:08:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.98,0:08:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.48,0:08:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Well, this woman's dog\Nhas gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.29,0:08:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.32,0:08:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.42,0:08:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nlet's inform the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.73,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already gone\Nto the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.89,0:08:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But that man's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an officer,\Nbut I can't count on him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.50,0:08:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an officer\Nwho hates dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I look for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Are you sure,\NMr. Newmeyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.74,0:08:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I was going to stroll\Naround town anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.31,0:08:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know Mrs. Hillman's dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.62,0:08:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that stupid dog\Nthat barks a lot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:09:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gone missing.\NDid you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.26,0:09:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.99,0:09:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.53,0:09:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, have you seen any\Nsuspicious strangers around town?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.97,0:09:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.00,0:09:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this? I thought that you\Nwere going to stay over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.78,0:09:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I'm staying at\Nthe Versteck Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.58,0:09:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that? They're stealing\Neveryone's customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that...\Nthe guests you have now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.72,0:09:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any. Thankfully,\Nit's quiet because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.73,0:09:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So if that dog barks as much as it did\Nwhen it was nearby, I'd know immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.30,0:09:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear barking today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.84,0:09:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.07,0:09:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.71,0:09:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard something that\Nsounded like a gunshot earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps some weirdo got angry at\Nthe dog for being noisy and shot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.86,0:10:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Good day. Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Lunge, Mr. Newmeyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.03,0:10:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Lunge,\Nwhere are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.\NHave you found any leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.37,0:10:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's continue\Nour search.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.26,0:10:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink. .. Give me a drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Dad, you shouldn't\Ndrink anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.69,0:10:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Go and buy me a drink already!\NA drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.10,0:10:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any money!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the money you earned\Nfrom working at that hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.41,0:11:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if I could buy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.12,0:11:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim, it's all right.\NThat's the money you've earned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.86,0:11:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You got beaten\Npretty badly today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.\NLet's go to my hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.52,0:11:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unusual to see someone\Neat as eagerly as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.22,0:11:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? It's really delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.92,0:11:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're just\Nregular sausages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.53,0:11:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the face I make\Nwhen things are delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.30,0:11:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.30,0:11:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a nice town.\NIt's quiet and there's good food.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.67,0:12:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so? I want to get out of\Nthis boring town as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.54,0:12:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there's someone wonderful\Nwho can take me away from this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Has someone wonderful\Ncome recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.\NEveryday, it's the same faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sick of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.49,0:12:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, about the dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've walked\Nthat dog before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.06,0:12:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Walked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When Mrs. Hillman had a cold,\NI walked him for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.30,0:12:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When I let him have some Eisbein\Nfrom my deli, he wouldn't let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.37,0:12:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He pulled it away\Nwith incredible force.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.64,0:12:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.01,0:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you've said, something\Nterrible has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dog.\NA dog has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear the gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.16,0:13:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that wasn't a gunshot.\NA car broke down by the highway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.76,0:13:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was probably the sound\Nof the car backfiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.67,0:13:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't hear a gunshot\Nin this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.42,0:13:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Things will get bad\Nif you frighten me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.33,0:13:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.64,0:13:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludwig...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.67,0:13:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.17,0:13:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You remembered that\Nyou buried that bone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.18,0:13:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, nice to see you,\NMr. Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.59,0:14:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like different clues\Nled us to the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.93,0:14:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And yourself?\NWhat are you doing in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.96,0:14:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a detective,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.33,0:14:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a hunch.\NYou have the air of a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.27,0:14:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look as if\Nyou're on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.44,0:14:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in Prague\Nnot too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.51,0:14:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There I heard information about\Nsomeone involved in a certain case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.02,0:14:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a tall man with a big bag.\NHe had a friendly, gentle smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,His hair color...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You completely match the data\NI have on this man, Mr. Newmeyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.84,0:14:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you come\Nto this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:15:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems we really were led to the\Nsame place through different clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.36,0:15:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that\Nyou can stop
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.20,0:15:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the terrible massacre that's\Nabout to happen in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.12,0:15:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Are you matching\Nlottery numbers again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your husband's going to\Nsweat away at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.82,0:15:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk so big.\NYou make so little.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.46,0:15:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our future will be bleak\Nunless we win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like that,\Nthen earn more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.37,0:15:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.17,0:15:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.74,0:15:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:15:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've won.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.84,0:15:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Won what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.61,0:16:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-The lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.48,0:16:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.71,0:16:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you put my bike?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.62,0:16:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know about\Nyour bike, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.92,0:16:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We threw away\Nsome trash, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.39,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You threw it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.46,0:16:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.29,0:16:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We tossed it in the Vampire's House\Nin the West Hills.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Vampire...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.97,0:16:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Go by yourself if\Nyou want to get it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.87,0:16:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know what'll\Nhappen to you if you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.49,0:16:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.59,0:16:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anyone come?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.60,0:16:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.90,0:16:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Be sure to put the chain on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.23,0:16:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.34,0:17:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sure this is\Nthe number, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.24,0:17:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I've checked it many times.\NI-I really won.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.21,0:17:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,20 million marks, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.38,0:17:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.52,0:17:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to the neighboring town.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.75,0:17:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Dear! This...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just in case. It's dangerous to be\Ncarrying that much money unarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.86,0:17:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you don't need it if we\Nmake sure no one knows about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.80,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No one knows the number of\Nthe lottery ticket you bought, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.14,0:17:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Actually,\Nwhen I bought that ticket...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.41,0:17:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The usual.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.52,0:17:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here you go.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.02,0:17:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You just don't win,\Ndo you, Mrs. Henich?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh. Hello, Mr. Conrad.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.89,0:17:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your husband was grumbling\Nabout your lotto obsession.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.23,0:18:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can use my birthday.\NMarch 2, 1945. It wins pretty often.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've hit the jackpot twice\Nat the horse races.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.08,0:18:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All right. Thank you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.08,0:18:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.52,0:18:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You used Conrad's birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.36,0:18:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If he sees the number\Nin the newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.23,0:18:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But he doesn't know what\Nnumbers you wrote, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.93,0:18:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Rumors about it might\Nbe spreading through town now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.97,0:18:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.40,0:18:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.44,0:18:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,On the way home, I stopped at the\Ngeneral store to buy some cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When I did, the girl from\Nthe sausage shop was looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.31,0:18:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! That's got to be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.42,0:18:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.18,0:19:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was throwing away the garbage,\Nthe drunk in the back was staring at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.12,0:19:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what that drunk would do\Nif he heard about the money!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.46,0:19:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.50,0:19:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,– But.. .\N– Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.53,0:19:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to\Nprotect ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.98,0:19:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vampire's House...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.77,0:19:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.06,0:20:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,From the looks of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.70,0:20:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's come here recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.94,0:20:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's uncompleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he stop drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.61,0:20:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Or could he not draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.12,0:20:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Why it's Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.62,0:20:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Newmeyer...\NMr. Lunge...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.22,0:20:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.56,0:20:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm... My bike... My friends said\Nthat they dumped my bike here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.53,0:20:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Your friends tricked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.97,0:20:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Your bike was in a bush at\Nthe bottom of the mountain path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.07,0:21:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.28,0:21:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like that cat was shot\Nwith a submachine gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They've already...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.52,0:21:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. They're nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.43,0:21:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A drawing of the twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.76,0:21:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.74,0:21:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.04,0:21:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.07,0:21:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.24,0:21:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.01,0:21:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.51,0:21:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're about ten-years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.72,0:21:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Those twins were about ten when\NI was in charge of Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.46,0:21:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,These are pictures drawn\Naround that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.56,0:21:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How many other pictures\Nlike this one are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.10,0:21:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times he\Ndrew it... he was never satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.27,0:22:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like there're going to\Nbe a lot of vines this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried about this year's\Nlingonberry crop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.53,0:22:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. I haven't seen you before.
